All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractGraph
The AbstractGraph class provides a base implementation for common graph operations.
Ant
The Ant class represents an ant in the Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) algorithm.
AntMoveEvent
The AntMoveEvent class represents an event where an ant moves along an edge in the graph.
Edge
The Edge class represents an edge in a graph.
EvaporationEvent
The EvaporationEvent class represents an event where the pheromone level on an edge evaporates.
Event
The Event class represents an event in the simulation.
Graph
The Graph class represents an unweighted graph.
HamiltonianCycle
The HamiltonianCycle class represents a Hamiltonian cycle in a graph.
IEdge
The IEdge interface represents an edge in a graph.
IEvent
The IEvent interface defines the contract for an event in the simulation.
IGraph
The IGraph interface represents a graph.
InputParameters
The InputParameters class represents the input parameters for the simulation.
Logger
The Logger class is a custom PrintStream that redirects output to two PrintStreams simultaneously.
Main
The simulation.Main class is the entry point of the program.
Node
The Node class represents a node in a graph.
PEC
The PEC (Pending Event Container) class represents the event control system in the simulation.
Pheromones
The Pheromones class represents the pheromone levels on edges in the graph.
Simulation
The Simulation class represents the simulation environment for the Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) algorithm.
SimulationReportEvent
The SimulationReportEvent class represents a report of the simulation at a specific time.
WeightedGraph
The WeightedGraph class represents a weighted graph.
